instruction:
A job description is a document that clearly states the requirements, duties, responsibilities, and skills required to perform a specific role. You need to write a job description based on the given information. You should describe responsibilities and duties in your job description in a logical order. Remember that potential employees often get their first impression of your company from your job description. So, the job description should convey the attractiveness of your company.

Company: [Company name]
Job: Software Engineer
Job Responsibilities:
Receive and perform code reviews with other engineers.
Write unit, integration, and end-to-end tests to verify functionality using automated testing frameworks such as Pytest.
Work collaboratively with fellow software engineers to build features requested by business stakeholders.
Participate in Agile teams to develop, test, and debug complex data processing pipelines and data analysis applications using big data processing systems such as Apache Spark.
Diagnose, debug, and perform root cause analysis of issues and defects.
Skills and experience that will lead to success:
Experience with a modern software programming language. We use Python, and Pyspark extensively.
Experience with cloud systems like AWS or Azure
Experience writing SQL queries 
Strong written and verbal communication skills
Eagerness to work in a highly-collaborative environment
Some visualization experience such as Tableau or PowerBI is helpful
output_1:
Job Title: Software Engineer

Job Summary:
We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Software Engineer to join our team. The successful candidate will be responsible for collaborating with other engineers to build features requested by business stakeholders, participating in Agile teams to develop, test, and debug complex data processing pipelines and data analysis applications using big data processing systems such as Apache Spark. The ideal candidate will have experience with modern software programming languages, cloud systems, and SQL queries, as well as strong written and verbal communication skills.

Job Responsibilities:

* Collaborate with other engineers to receive and perform code reviews
* Write unit, integration, and end-to-end tests to verify functionality using automated testing frameworks such as Pytest
* Participate in Agile teams to develop, test, and debug complex data processing pipelines and data analysis applications using big data processing systems such as Apache Spark
* Diagnose, debug, and perform root cause analysis of issues and defects
* Participate in code reviews and provide constructive feedback to improve the quality of the codebase
* Collaborate with other teams to ensure that software solutions meet business requirements
* Stay up-to-date with the latest trends and best practices in software engineering

Skills and Experience:

* Strong experience with a modern software programming language, preferably Python and Pyspark
* Experience with cloud systems such as AWS or Azure
* Experience writing SQL queries
* Strong written and verbal communication skills
* Eagerness to work in a highly-collaborative environment
* Some visualization experience such as Tableau or PowerBI is helpful
* Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field

We offer a competitive salary and benefits package, as well as opportunities for professional growth and development. If you are passionate about software engineering and want to work in a dynamic and collaborative environment, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.
output_2:
Job Description: Software Engineer

Job Responsibilities:

As a Software Engineer at [Company name], you will be responsible for collaborating with a team of engineers to develop and maintain our data processing pipelines and analysis applications. You will receive and perform code reviews, write unit, integration, and end-to-end tests, and diagnose, debug, and perform root cause analysis of issues and defects. You will work with big data processing systems such as Apache Spark, and participate in Agile teams to build features requested by business stakeholders.

Additionally, you will be expected to have experience with modern programming languages, such as Python, and Pyspark. You should also have experience with cloud systems, such as AWS or Azure, and be proficient in writing SQL queries. Strong written and verbal communication skills are essential for working in a highly-collaborative environment, and experience with visualization tools such as Tableau or PowerBI is helpful.

Skills and Experience:

To be successful as a Software Engineer at [Company name], you should have the following skills and experience:

* Experience with a modern software programming language, specifically Python and Pyspark
* Experience with cloud systems, such as AWS or Azure
* Proficiency in writing SQL queries
* Strong written and verbal communication skills
* Experience working in a highly-collaborative environment
* Experience with visualization tools, such as Tableau or PowerBI

We are an innovative company that values diversity and fosters a culture of collaboration, creativity, and continuous learning. As a member of our team, you will have the opportunity to work on exciting projects, collaborate with talented professionals, and grow your skills and experience. We offer a competitive salary, comprehensive benefits, and a dynamic work environment. If you are passionate about technology and eager to work with a team of talented professionals, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.

instruction:
Write a section for a blog post and try to cover all of the provided information about this section in your text.

Blog Topic: 7 Fall Fashion Trends Worth Taking on Your Trip
Section Title: Trusty Jeans
Main point of the section: jeans can be worn all year and look good with everything .
output_1:
When it comes to fashion, it's important to have pieces that can transition seamlessly from season to season. One such piece that is always a reliable and versatile option is a pair of trusty jeans. Whether you're hitting the town or exploring a new city, a good pair of jeans can be dressed up or down to fit the occasion.

This fall, jeans are still a staple in many people's wardrobes. They come in a variety of washes, fits, and styles, so there's something for everyone. Darker washes and more relaxed fits are popular this season, but don't be afraid to mix it up with a lighter wash or a more tailored fit.

One of the great things about jeans is that they can be worn with just about anything. A simple t-shirt and sneakers is a classic look, but you can also dress them up with a blazer or heels for a more polished look. Jeans also look great with boots, booties, or sneakers, so they're a great option for a casual weekend getaway or a more formal trip.

In addition to being versatile, jeans are also comfortable and durable. They're a great option for travel because they're easy to pack and can withstand being stuffed in a bag for long periods of time. Plus, they're a great option for exploring a new city because they're easy to move around in.

Overall, jeans are a great option for anyone looking for a reliable and versatile piece to add to their fall wardrobe. They're comfortable, durable, and can be dressed up or down to fit any occasion. So, next time you're packing for a trip, consider adding a pair of trusty jeans to your suitcase.
output_2:
Trusty Jeans: A Timeless Fall Fashion Trend

One of the most versatile and timeless fashion pieces that can be worn all year round is the trusty pair of jeans. This fall, jeans are still a must-have item in every fashionista's wardrobe. They can be dressed up or down, and can be paired with almost anything, making them a perfect addition to your travel wardrobe.

This fall, denim styles come in a variety of washes, colors, and textures that are perfect for the season. Darker washes, like deep blues and blacks, are in, as are distressed denim and faded hues. If you're looking for a more classic look, consider a pair of clean, straight-leg jeans in a classic blue wash.

Jeans are also a great option for travel because they are comfortable and easy to move around in. You can wear them with a graphic t-shirt and sneakers for a casual look, or dress them up with a blouse and heels for a more polished look. Jeans can also be dressed down with a sweater, scarf, and ankle boots for a cozy, chic vibe.

When traveling, it's important to pack versatile pieces that can be worn in a variety of settings. Jeans are a perfect example of a piece that can be dressed up or down and can be worn for both casual and formal occasions. They are also a great option for exploring a new city, as they are comfortable and easy to move around in.

In conclusion, trusty jeans are a timeless fall fashion trend that can be worn all year round, and are a must-have in every fashionista's wardrobe. They are versatile, comfortable, and can be paired with almost anything, making them the perfect addition to your travel wardrobe.

instruction:
Using the provided topic as a starting point, brainstorm ideas for videos that can be made about it on YouTube.

In spite of the fact that procrastination feels bad to you, why do you do it?
output_1:
1. The Psychology of Procrastination: Understanding why we put off tasks and how to overcome it.
2. The Power of Habits: How procrastination can be a result of ingrained habits and how to change them.
3. The Procrastination Paradox: Why we often feel more productive when we procrastinate.
4. The Benefits of Breaking Tasks: How breaking down large tasks into smaller, more manageable ones can help with procrastination.
5. The Importance of Time Management: How to prioritize tasks and use time effectively to reduce procrastination.
6. The Pros and Cons of Procrastination: Examining the positive and negative effects of procrastination on our lives.
7. The Art of Self-Motivation: How to find the motivation to start and complete tasks despite procrastination.
8. The Role of Emotions: How emotions like fear, anxiety, and perfectionism can contribute to procrastination.
9. The Power of Accountability: How to enlist the help of others to overcome procrastination.
10. The Science of Procrastination: Exploring the latest research on why we procrastinate and what can be done to overcome it.
output_2:
1. Understanding the psychology behind procrastination: This video can explore the reasons behind why people procrastinate by analyzing the psychological factors that contribute to this behavior. It can discuss the role of fear, lack of motivation, and self-doubt in procrastination.

2. Procrastination and productivity: This video can delve into the relationship between procrastination and productivity, explaining how procrastination can negatively impact productivity levels. It can suggest strategies for overcoming procrastination and increasing productivity.

3. Breaking the cycle of procrastination: This video can offer practical tips and techniques for breaking the cycle of procrastination. It can discuss the importance of setting realistic goals, creating a structured schedule, and utilizing time-management techniques to overcome procrastination.

4. The impact of technology on procrastination: This video can examine how technology can influence procrastination. It can discuss the potential drawbacks of constant connectivity and the ease of distraction that technology provides. It can also offer suggestions for minimizing the negative impact of technology on procrastination.

5. Procrastination and self-care: This video can explore the connection between procrastination and self-care, emphasizing the importance of taking care of oneself in order to overcome procrastination. It can discuss the role of self-care in building self-confidence and increasing motivation.

6. Overcoming procrastination with mindfulness: This video can introduce mindfulness techniques as a way to overcome procrastination. It can discuss the benefits of mindfulness in reducing stress and anxiety, and improving focus and concentration. It can also offer practical tips for incorporating mindfulness into daily life.

7. Procrastination and self-discipline: This video can delve into the importance of self-discipline in overcoming procrastination. It can discuss the role of self-discipline in setting goals, creating a schedule, and staying motivated. It can also offer tips for developing self-discipline.

The word "cacophony" refers to a harsh, discordant mixture of sounds. In this sentence, the student is trying to study despite the loud sounds around them. The other options do not fit the context of the sentence. "Difficult subject" would not necessarily cause the student to try to study despite loud sounds. "Late hour" would not necessarily cause the student to try to study despite loud sounds. "Low lighting" would not necessarily cause the student to try to study despite loud sounds.
output_2:
A. Loud sounds

In the sentence, the word "cacophony" refers to a harsh, discordant mixture of sounds. This means that the sounds are loud and displeasing to the ear. Therefore, the correct answer is option A, "loud sounds."

3. Suffering: Adversity can refer to any type of suffering or hardship, while suffering specifically refers to the emotional or physical pain caused by such hardship.

These words are similar in meaning, but adversity often implies a more prolonged or severe period of difficulty, while hardship and difficulty may refer to specific, short-term challenges. Struggle and challenge can also refer to a more active and ongoing process, whereas adversity may imply a more passive or enduring situation.

instruction:
Discuss the origins and history of the word that has been given to you.

oblique
output_1:
The word "oblique" comes from the Latin word "obliquus," which means "sloping" or "askew." The word entered the English language in the 14th century, and has since been used to describe a variety of things that are slanted or at an angle.

In its most basic sense, "oblique" refers to something that is not straight or perpendicular. This can apply to physical objects, such as a building with an oblique angle, or to abstract concepts, such as an oblique approach to a problem.

In art and design, "oblique" is often used to describe a diagonal line or shape. In music, an oblique interval is one that is not a perfect fifth or octave. In literature, an oblique reference is a subtle or indirect allusion to something.

Overall, the word "oblique" has been used in a variety of contexts throughout history, reflecting its versatility and the many different ways in which it can be applied.
output_2:
The word "oblique" comes from the Latin word "obliquus," which means "slanted," "crooked," or "askew." The Latin word is derived from the Latin verb "obliquare," which means "to turn aside" or "to deviate from a straight line."

The term "oblique" has been in use since the 14th century and has been used to describe something that is slanted or at an angle that is not perpendicular. In the context of geometry, an oblique angle is an angle that is not a right angle (90 degrees). In art and design, an oblique line is a line that is drawn at an angle to the horizon, creating a sense of movement and energy.

In literature, the word "oblique" has been used to describe characters or situations that are not straightforward or direct. In politics, the term "oblique" has been used to describe a political strategy that is indirect or subtle. In general, the word "oblique" is often used to describe something that is not straight forward or simple, but instead, is indirect or complex.

instruction: Write a step-by-step guide for resolving GitHub merge conflicts.
output_1:
GitHub merge conflicts can be a frustrating experience, but with the right approach, they can be resolved quickly and easily. Here is a step-by-step guide for resolving GitHub merge conflicts:

1. Identify the conflict: The first step is to identify the conflict. This can be done by opening the file in question and looking for lines with a "<<<<<<<", "=======", and ">>>>>>>" notation. These notations indicate that there is a conflict in that section of the file.

2. Open a pull request: Once you have identified the conflict, open a pull request to merge the changes into your repository. This will allow you to see the changes that are causing the conflict.

3. Review the changes: Carefully review the changes that are causing the conflict. Look for any lines that are different between the two branches and try to determine which changes should be kept and which should be discarded.

4. Resolve the conflict: Once you have determined which changes should be kept and which should be discarded, you can resolve the conflict. This can be done by editing the file and removing the conflict markers.

5. Commit the changes: After resolving the conflict, commit the changes to your branch. Make sure to include a meaningful commit message that describes the changes you made.

6. Push the changes: Once you have committed the changes, push them to your branch. This will update your local repository with the changes.

7. Merge the branch: Finally, you can merge the branch into your repository. This will apply the changes to your repository and resolve the conflict.

By following these steps, you can easily resolve GitHub merge conflicts and keep your repository up-to-date.
output_2:

2. Open the Conflicting File: Double-click on the file to open it in your default text editor. This will display the conflicting sections in a different color, making it easier to see where the conflicts are.

3. Resolve the Conflicts: Go through the conflicting sections and try to resolve them. Look for lines that are the same on both sides and remove the conflict markers. You can also use your preferred merge tool to automatically resolve the conflicts.

4. Stage the Changes: Once you have resolved the conflicts, stage the changes by right-clicking on the file in the staging area and selecting "Add Changes to Stage."

5. Commit the Changes: In the commit message box, describe the changes you made to resolve the conflicts. Then, click on the "Commit to Master" button.

6. Push the Changes: In the top right corner of the screen, click on the "Push origin" button. This will push the changes to the remote repository on GitHub.

7. Verify the Changes: Go to the repository's commit history and verify that the conflict has been resolved.

By following these steps, you can easily resolve GitHub merge conflicts and keep your repository up-to-date.

instruction:
One or more jobs can be run automatically by a workflow. The workflows are defined in the repository as YAML files and will run if an event occurs in the repository, as well as manually, or on a certain schedule.
Bring an example of a workflow that demonstrate the CI/CD features of GitHub Actions.
output_1:
Sure, here's an example of a GitHub Actions workflow that demonstrates CI/CD features:
```yaml
name: CI/CD workflow

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
  pull_request:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
    - name: Checkout code
      uses: actions/checkout@v2
    - name: Set up Node.js
      uses: actions/setup-node@v2
      with:
        node-version: 14.x
    - name: Run tests
      run: |
        npm install
        npm test
    - name: Build package
      run: |
        npm run build
    - name: Publish package
      uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v3
      with:
        github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        publish_dir: ./dist
```
In this workflow, the `build` job runs on the `main` branch when a push event occurs or when a pull request is opened against the `main` branch. The job checks out the code, sets up Node.js, runs tests, builds the package, and publishes it to the GitHub Pages.

The `on` section specifies the events that trigger the workflow. In this example, the workflow runs on push events to the `main` branch and pull request events to the `main` branch.

The `jobs` section defines the jobs that run in the workflow. The `build` job is the only job defined in this example.

The `steps` section defines the steps that run in the job. The `Checkout code` step checks out the code from the repository. The `Set up Node.js` step installs Node.js and sets the version to 14.x. The `Run tests` step runs the tests using `npm test`. The `Build package` step runs `npm run build` to build the package. The `Publish package` step uses the `peaceiris/actions-gh-pages` action to publish the package to GitHub Pages.

This workflow demonstrates how GitHub Actions can be used for continuous integration and continuous deployment by automatically building and publishing the package to GitHub Pages whenever changes are pushed to the `main` branch.
output_2:
Here is an example of a GitHub Action workflow that demonstrates CI/CD features:
```yaml
name: CI/CD Workflow

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
    - name: Checkout code
      uses: actions/checkout@v2
    - name: Build application
      run: |
        npm install
        npm run build
```
This workflow will run automatically when a push event occurs on the main branch, and it will also run when a pull request is opened or updated on the main branch. The workflow will check out the code from the repository and then run the build command to install dependencies and build the application.

instruction:
Write a short analysis of the cinematography in the movie.

Dead Poets Society
output_1:
Dead Poets Society is a 1989 American drama film directed by Peter Weir and starring Robin Williams. The cinematography in the movie is a significant aspect of its overall aesthetic and narrative. The film is set in a prestigious boys' prep school in the 1950s, and the cinematography captures the period's aesthetic, with its focus on order, discipline, and conformity. The camera work is often static, with long takes and a focus on the characters' faces, emphasizing their emotions and inner thoughts.

The film's cinematography also highlights the contrast between the school's rigid structure and the characters' desire for individuality and self-expression. The use of lighting and color is also significant, with the school's interiors often being dimly lit and the exteriors featuring muted colors, reflecting the film's themes of conformity and repression.

The film's most iconic scene, the "carpe diem" sequence, is a masterful example of the cinematography's ability to convey the characters' emotions and the film's themes. The scene features the boys standing on their desks, reciting a poem, and the camera work captures the sense of exhilaration and rebellion that the scene represents.

Overall, the cinematography in Dead Poets Society is a crucial element of the film's aesthetic and narrative, capturing the period's aesthetic, highlighting the contrast between conformity and individuality, and conveying the characters' emotions and themes.
output_2:
Dead Poets Society is a film that is known for its captivating cinematography, which contributes significantly to its overall mood and atmosphere. The movie, directed by Peter Weir, features a range of techniques that effectively convey the themes and emotions of the story. 

One of the key elements of the cinematography is the use of long takes and sweeping camera movements. This technique is used to create a sense of grandeur and to emphasize the vast, open spaces of the boarding school where the story takes place. Additionally, the camera often moves in a fluid, almost dreamlike manner, creating a sense of disorientation and heightening the emotional impact of certain scenes.

The film also makes use of a variety of lighting techniques to enhance the mood and tone of each scene. For example, the use of low-key lighting during the more somber moments creates a sense of foreboding and tension, while the brighter, more vibrant lighting during the more uplifting scenes emphasizes the characters' passion and energy.

Overall, the cinematography in Dead Poets Society is a striking and effective way of bringing the story to life. Through its use of visual elements, the film successfully conveys the emotions and themes of the story, making it a memorable and impactful cinematic experience.

instruction:
Answer the following question.

How do I compare strings in Java?
I've been using the == operator in my program to compare all my strings so far. However, I ran into a bug, changed one of them into .equals() instead, and it fixed the bug.
Is == bad? When should it and should it not be used? What's the difference?
output_1:
The == operator compares the memory addresses of two objects, not their values. This means that if two objects have the same value, but different memory addresses, they will be considered different by the == operator.

The .equals() method, on the other hand, compares the values of two objects. This means that if two objects have the same value, they will be considered equal by the .equals() method, regardless of their memory addresses.

In general, it is recommended to use the .equals() method to compare strings in Java, rather than the == operator. The == operator can be misleading and can lead to bugs in your code.

It is also important to note that the .equals() method is not the same as the == operator for objects of type String. The .equals() method for String objects compares the characters of the strings, not the memory addresses.

In summary, the == operator should not be used to compare strings in Java, as it compares the memory addresses of two objects, not their values. Instead, use the .equals() method to compare the values of two strings.
output_2:
The == operator is not recommended for comparing strings in Java because it compares the object references, not the string values. This means that two strings with the same value can have different object references and therefore, be considered different.

The correct way to compare strings in Java is to use the .equals() method. This method compares the actual string values, not the object references, so it will correctly determine if two strings are equal or not.

In general, the == operator should only be used when comparing object references, not string values. It should not be used for comparing strings, as demonstrated in the example.

Problem Statement:

You are given an array of integers and a target value. Your task is to find the minimum number of jumps required to reach the target value, where a jump is moving to the next highest element in the array. You can only move up and cannot move down.

Input:

target = 8

The problem:

Given a list of integers, find the longest subsequence of these integers that add up to a given target.

Constraints:

* The input list contains integers between -1000 and 1000.
* The target number is also an integer between -1000 and 1000.
* The longest subsequence must be found in a time complexity of O(n).

Example:

Input: list = [-1, 2, 1, -3, 4, -1, 2, 1]
target = 7

The longest subsequence that adds up to the target is: [-1, 2, 1]

Solution:

To solve this problem using dynamic programming, we can use the fact that the problem can be broken down into a 2D table where the rows represent the integers in the input list and the columns represent the integers in the target. Each cell in the table would represent the length of the longest subsequence that adds up to the sum of the row and column indices.

The base case is represented by the first row and first column, where the length of the longest subsequence that adds up to 0 is 0.

The recurrence relation is represented by the following formula:

MaxLength = Max(MaxLength of the first row + 1, MaxLength of the first column + 1, MaxLength of the next row + MaxLength of the next column - Sum of the row and column indices)

For example, in the above example, the first row is [1] and the first column is [1]. The maximum length of the longest subsequence that adds up to 7 is 3. Therefore, the base case is 0 and the recurrence relation is MaxLength = Max(1, 1, 3 + 1 - 7) = 3.

Constraints:

* The table must be of size (n+1) x (m+1) and the time complexity must be O(n+m).
* The table must be filled in such a way that the maximum length of the longest subsequence is stored in the last cell of the last row and the last column.

instruction:
You are given a programming problem and its implementation. Analyze the problem and implementation and explain the algorithm and approach used to solve the problem.

Table: Person
| Column Name | Type     |
| personId          | int         |
| lastName         | varchar |
| firstName         | varchar |
personId is the primary key column for this table.
This table contains information about the ID of some persons and their first and last names.
Table: Address
| Column Name | Type     |
| addressId        | int         |
| personId          | int         |
| city                   | varchar|
| state                | varchar |
addressId is the primary key column for this table.
Each row of this table contains information about the city and state of one person with ID = PersonId.
Write an SQL query to report the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table. If the address of a personId is not present in the Address table, report null instead.
Return the result table in any order.
Implementation:
select FirstName, LastName, City, State
from Person left join Address
on Person.PersonId = Address.PersonId
;
output_1:
The given problem is to write an SQL query to report the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table. If the address of a personId is not present in the Address table, report null instead. The result table should be returned in any order.

The implementation provided is a SQL query that uses a left join to join the Person and Address tables on the PersonId column. The left join ensures that all rows from the Person table are included in the result, even if there is no matching row in the Address table for that person.

The query selects the FirstName, LastName, City, and State columns from the Person and Address tables. The result of the query will be a table that contains the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table, along with null values for any rows where there is no matching address in the Address table.

The query returns the result table in any order, which means that the order of the rows in the result table is not guaranteed. If you want to specify a particular order for the rows, you can use an ORDER BY clause in the query.

Overall, the implementation is a simple and effective way to solve the given problem. It uses a left join to combine the Person and Address tables, and selects the relevant columns to get the desired information. The result is a table that contains the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table, along with null values for any missing addresses.
output_2:
The given problem involves joining two tables, Person and Address, based on their primary key, personId, and returning the first name, last name, city, and state of each person from the Person table. If the address of a person is not present in the Address table, the query returns null instead.

The implementation of this problem uses a left join to join the two tables and return all rows from the Person table, along with the matching rows from the Address table. If there is no matching row in the Address table for a person, the query returns null values for the city and state columns.

The SQL query used to solve this problem is:
```
SELECT FirstName, LastName, City, State
FROM Person
LEFT JOIN Address
ON Person.PersonId = Address.PersonId;
```
This query uses a left join to combine the data from both tables. The left join ensures that all rows from the Person table are included in the result set, even if there is no matching row in the Address table for that person.

The result set contains the first name, last name, city, and state columns from the Person table and the city and state columns from the Address table. If there is no matching row in the Address table for a person, the city and state columns will be null.

instruction:
Summarize the article you have been given in a brief manner.

Mathematics and art are related in a variety of ways. Mathematics has itself been described as an art motivated by beauty. Mathematics can be discerned in arts such as music, dance, painting, architecture, sculpture, and textiles. This article focuses, however, on mathematics in the visual arts.
Mathematics and art have a long historical relationship. Artists have used mathematics since the 4th century BC when the Greek sculptor Polykleitos wrote his Canon, prescribing proportions conjectured to have been based on the ratio 1:√2 for the ideal male nude. Persistent popular claims have been made for the use of the golden ratio in ancient art and architecture, without reliable evidence. In the Italian Renaissance, Luca Pacioli wrote the influential treatise De divina proportione (1509), illustrated with woodcuts by Leonardo da Vinci, on the use of the golden ratio in art. Another Italian painter, Piero della Francesca, developed Euclid's ideas on perspective in treatises such as De Prospectiva Pingendi, and in his paintings. The engraver Albrecht Dürer made many references to mathematics in his work Melencolia I. In modern times, the graphic artist M. C. Escher made intensive use of tessellation and hyperbolic geometry, with the help of the mathematician H. S. M. Coxeter, while the De Stijl movement led by Theo van Doesburg and Piet Mondrian explicitly embraced geometrical forms. Mathematics has inspired textile arts such as quilting, knitting, cross-stitch, crochet, embroidery, weaving, Turkish and other carpet-making, as well as kilim. In Islamic art, symmetries are evident in forms as varied as Persian girih and Moroccan zellige tilework, Mughal jali pierced stone screens, and widespread muqarnas vaulting.
output_1: The article discusses the relationship between mathematics and art, specifically in the visual arts. It highlights the historical use of mathematics in art, from the Greek sculptor Polykleitos' Canon to the Italian Renaissance, and the influence of mathematicians and artists such as Leonardo da Vinci, Piero della Francesca, Albrecht Dürer, M. C. Escher, and Theo van Doesburg and Piet Mondrian. The article also mentions the use of mathematics in textile arts and Islamic art.
output_2: The article discusses the relationship between mathematics and art, specifically in the visual arts. It highlights the use of mathematics in various forms of art throughout history, including sculpture, painting, architecture, and textiles. It also mentions the influence of mathematicians and artists working together, such as M.C. Escher and H.S.M. Coxeter. The article concludes by emphasizing the presence of mathematics in textile arts and Islamic art.

The "fair trade" movement, also known as the "trade justice" movement, promotes the use of labour, environmental and social standards for the production of commodities, particularly those exported from the Third and Second Worlds to the First World. Such ideas have also sparked a debate on whether trade itself should be codified as a human right.
output_1:
The "fair trade" movement, also known as the "trade justice" movement, is a social movement that advocates for the use of labour, environmental, and social standards for the production of commodities, particularly those exported from the Third and Second Worlds to the First World. The movement seeks to promote fair and equitable trade practices that prioritize the well-being of workers, communities, and the environment.

The fair trade movement has gained significant traction in recent years, as consumers have become increasingly aware of the negative impacts of conventional trade practices on workers, the environment, and local communities. Conventional trade practices often prioritize the interests of multinational corporations and result in the exploitation of workers, environmental degradation, and the destruction of local communities.

The fair trade movement seeks to address these issues by promoting the use of fair labor standards, such as fair wages, safe working conditions, and the protection of workers' rights. It also promotes the use of environmentally sustainable practices, such as the use of renewable resources and the reduction of waste. Additionally, the fair trade movement seeks to promote social justice by supporting marginalized communities and promoting gender equality.

The fair trade movement has also sparked a debate on whether trade itself should be codified as a human right. The movement argues that access to fair and equitable trade practices is a fundamental human right that should be recognized and protected by international law. This view is based on the belief that trade should be a means of promoting human well-being and development, rather than a tool for exploitation and oppression.

In conclusion, the fair trade movement is a social movement that advocates for the use of fair labor, environmental, and social standards for the production of commodities. The movement seeks to promote fair and equitable trade practices that prioritize the well-being of workers, communities, and the environment. The fair trade movement has also sparked a debate on whether trade itself should be codified as a human right.
output_2:
The "fair trade" movement, also known as the "trade justice" movement, seeks to promote socially and environmentally responsible practices in the production and trade of goods, particularly those originating from the developing countries, often referred to as the Third and Second Worlds, to the developed countries, known as the First World. This movement advocates for the implementation of stringent labour, environmental and social standards for the production of commodities to ensure that the people involved in their creation, including workers, farmers and local communities, are treated fairly and sustainably.

The concept of fair trade has been a subject of intense debate, with some arguing that the principles of fair trade should be recognized as a fundamental human right. This would ensure that all individuals, regardless of their geographical location, have access to goods and services that are produced in a manner that respects their dignity, rights and wellbeing. By recognizing fair trade as a human right, it would ensure that all individuals have the opportunity to participate in a global economy that is equitable, just, and sustainable.

The fair trade movement has been instrumental in promoting ethical and sustainable practices in the production of goods, particularly in the agricultural sector. The movement has also played a crucial role in empowering marginalized communities, particularly in the developing world, by providing them with a fair and sustainable source of income. By recognizing fair trade as a human right, it would further empower these communities and ensure that they are able to benefit from the global economy in a meaningful way.

In conclusion, the fair trade movement is a crucial part of the global effort to promote sustainable and equitable practices in the production and trade of goods. By recognizing fair trade as a human right, it would further empower marginalized communities and ensure that all individuals are able to participate in a global economy that is just, sustainable, and equitable.

instruction: Give students tips on how to keep their nerves under control during class presentations.
output_1:
Here are some tips to help students keep their nerves under control during class presentations:

1. Practice, practice, practice: The more you practice your presentation, the more comfortable you will feel when it's time to deliver it. Rehearse in front of a mirror, with a friend or family member, or even by yourself until you feel confident.

2. Use positive self-talk: Instead of focusing on the negative thoughts that may be causing your nerves, try to reframe them in a positive way. For example, instead of thinking "I'm going to mess this up," tell yourself "I'm going to do my best and it's okay if I make a mistake."

3. Take deep breaths: When you start to feel nervous, take a few deep breaths to help calm your nerves. Inhale deeply through your nose and exhale slowly through your mouth.

4. Focus on your audience: Instead of focusing on your own nerves, try to focus on your audience. Connect with them and try to make a connection with them. This will help you feel more comfortable and confident.

5. Use visualization techniques: Visualize yourself delivering a successful presentation. Imagine yourself speaking confidently and clearly, and receiving positive feedback from your audience.

6. Remember that it's okay to make mistakes: Nobody is perfect, and it's okay to make mistakes during a presentation. If you do make a mistake, don't let it throw you off. Simply correct it and move on.

7. Take care of yourself: Make sure you are well-rested, well-fed, and hydrated before your presentation. This will help you feel more energized and focused.

By following these tips, you can help keep your nerves under control during class presentations and deliver a successful presentation.
output_2:
1. Practice, practice, practice: The more familiar you are with your presentation, the more confident you will feel. Practice in front of friends, family, or even alone until you are comfortable with the material.

2. Use visual aids: Visual aids like slides or props can help you stay focused and calm. They can also help you to keep your audience engaged and make the presentation more interesting.

3. Deep breathing: Take a few deep breaths before you begin your presentation. This can help you to calm down and focus your mind.

4. Stay positive: Focus on the positive aspects of your presentation and try to stay optimistic. Remember that you have prepared well and that you have something valuable to share with your audience.

5. Relax your body: Try to relax your body as much as possible. Stand up straight, uncross your arms, and avoid fidgeting. This will help you to look more confident and in control.

6. Take breaks: If you feel yourself starting to feel nervous, take a short break. Take a few deep breaths, stretch, or walk around the room. This can help you to regain your composure and refocus your energy.

7. Remember: Remember that it's okay to make mistakes. Nobody is perfect, and mistakes are an opportunity to learn and grow. Stay calm, be yourself, and enjoy the experience.

instruction:
Provide a detailed explanation of the steps that are required in order to construct the given project.

Steam Engine Using an Empty Beer Can
output_1:
Constructing a steam engine using an empty beer can is a fun and educational project that can be done with basic materials. Here are the steps to follow:

1. Gather materials: You will need an empty beer can, a cork, a rubber band, a piece of copper wire, a nail, a piece of cloth, and some water.

2. Prepare the beer can: Cut off the top of the beer can using a can opener. Make sure to leave enough of the can intact so that it can be reused.

3. Create a seal: Place the cork in the opening of the beer can and wrap the rubber band around it to create a seal.

4. Create a valve: Cut a small hole in the cloth and place it over the cork. The hole should be small enough to allow steam to escape but large enough to allow air to enter.

5. Create a steam chamber: Cut a small hole in the side of the beer can and insert the copper wire. This will create a steam chamber that will allow steam to build up and push the piston.

6. Attach the piston: Place the nail in the center of the cloth and attach it to the copper wire. This will act as the piston.

7. Fill the can with water: Fill the beer can with water until it is about half full.

8. Light the fire: Light a small fire using a match or lighter.

9. Heat the can: Place the beer can over the fire until it starts to steam.

10. Observe the piston: As the steam builds up in the can, it will push the piston, causing it to move back and forth.

11. Experiment with different sizes and shapes of cans: You can experiment with different sizes and shapes of cans to see how they affect the performance of the steam engine.

12. Clean up: Once you are finished, make sure to dispose of the materials properly and clean up any mess.

This project is a great way to learn about the principles of steam power and how they can be used to create movement. It is also a fun and creative way to recycle an empty beer can.

2. Design the steam engine:

First, draw a simple diagram of the steam engine on the piece of paper. It should consist of a cylinder, a piston, and a connecting rod. The cylinder should be the empty beer can, while the piston and connecting rod can be made using the piece of wood or plastic.

3. Assemble the steam engine:

Place the cork on the bottom of the beer can, and then use the needle to poke a small hole in the cork. This will allow air to escape when the steam is released.

4. Fit the cork into the opening at the top of the can, and then place the nail through the cork and into the can. This will act as a valve to control the flow of steam.

5. Attach the piston and connecting rod to the can by gluing or taping them in place. The piston should be positioned so that it fits snugly inside the can, while the connecting rod should be attached to the can at one end and to the piston at the other.

6. Fill the can with water:

Using the piece of wood or plastic, cut a small hole in the bottom of the can. Then, carefully pour the water into the can through the hole.

Use a lighter or a match to light the paper, which should be placed on top of the can. As the paper burns, it will produce heat, which will cause the water inside the can to boil.

instruction: Develop a mental exercise that can help people manage their anxiety and explain how it works.
output_1:
One mental exercise that can help people manage their anxiety is called "grounding." Grounding is a technique that helps individuals focus on the present moment and calm their racing thoughts. Here's how it works:

1. Start by finding a comfortable position, either sitting or standing.
2. Take a deep breath in and out, and focus on your breath as you inhale and exhale.
3. Begin to notice your surroundings, paying attention to the sights, sounds, and smells around you.
4. Identify five things you can see, four things you can hear, three things you can feel, two things you can taste, and one thing you can smell.
5. Once you've identified these five sensory experiences, try to engage with them fully. For example, if you see a tree, try to notice the texture of its leaves, the color of its bark, and the shape of its branches.
6. As you engage with your surroundings, try to let go of any thoughts or worries that come up. Instead, focus on the present moment and the sensory experiences around you.
7. Continue this exercise for a few minutes, until you feel more calm and centered.

Grounding works by helping individuals shift their focus from their racing thoughts and worries to the present moment. By engaging with their senses and paying attention to their surroundings, individuals can calm their minds and reduce their anxiety levels. Additionally, grounding can help individuals become more mindful and aware of their thoughts and emotions, which can lead to greater self-awareness and emotional regulation.
output_2:
One mental exercise that can help people manage their anxiety is called "The 54321 Technique." This technique involves focusing on five specific body parts, counting backwards from five to one, and then repeating a calming word or phrase to yourself.

Here's how it works:

1. Start by finding a comfortable seated position.
2. Begin by focusing on your feet and taking a deep breath.
3. As you inhale, visualize a bright, warm light filling your feet and toes.
4. Exhale, and as you let go of the breath, imagine the tension leaving your feet and toes.
5. Repeat this process for each of the four body parts: ankles, knees, stomach, and hands.
6. When you reach the fifth body part, which is your head, take a deep breath and repeat the calming word or phrase to yourself. This can be any phrase that helps you feel calm and centered, such as "I am safe," "I am calm," or "I am in control."
7. Repeat this process for several minutes, focusing on your breath and the calming phrase, until you feel more relaxed and centered.

The 54321 Technique works by helping individuals focus on their body and become more aware of their physical sensations. By visualizing and releasing tension in each body part, they can release physical anxiety and feel more grounded and centered. The calming phrase can also help shift their mental focus and create a sense of calm and control. Over time, this exercise can become a helpful tool for managing anxiety in daily life.

instruction: Plan an agenda for the daily standup meetings. Assign a time duration to each topic on the agenda.
output_1:
Here is a sample agenda for a daily standup meeting, with suggested time durations for each topic:

1. **Introduction (5 minutes)**: Start the meeting by asking each team member to briefly introduce themselves and their tasks for the day.
2. **What did you do yesterday? (5 minutes)**: Each team member should briefly describe what they accomplished the previous day and what they plan to work on today.
3. **What are you working on now? (5 minutes)**: Each team member should describe what they are currently working on and any obstacles or challenges they are facing.
4. **What do you need help with? (5 minutes)**: Each team member should ask for help or resources they need to complete their tasks.
5. **Any blockers? (5 minutes)**: If any team member is blocked from moving forward on their tasks, they should describe the blocker and ask for help to remove it.
6. **Any other business? (5 minutes)**: If there is any other business to discuss, such as upcoming deadlines or changes to the project, this is the time to do so.
7. **Next steps (5 minutes)**: Each team member should describe their next steps and when they expect to complete them.
8. **Meeting adjourned (5 minutes)**: The meeting should be adjourned after the last team member has finished their next steps.

Note: The time durations for each topic are just a suggestion and can be adjusted based on the needs of the team and the project.
output_2:
Here is a suggested agenda for a daily stand-up meeting with a recommended time duration for each topic:

1. **Introduction (2 minutes)**: Start the meeting by having each team member briefly introduce themselves and their tasks for the day.

2. **What did you do yesterday? (5 minutes)**: Each team member should briefly share what they accomplished the previous day, including any roadblocks or obstacles they encountered.

3. **What will you do today? (5 minutes)**: Each team member should provide an update on what they plan to accomplish today, including any new tasks or changes to their previous plans.

4. **Blockers and impediments (5 minutes)**: If any team members are facing obstacles or blockers that are preventing them from completing their work, they should bring them up in this section. The team can then discuss potential solutions and decide on a course of action.

5. **Review of progress (5 minutes)**: The team leader should briefly review the progress of the project as a whole, highlighting any notable achievements or areas that need more attention.

6. **Open discussion (5 minutes)**: This section is reserved for any other topics or concerns that team members want to bring up. This could include updates from other departments, requests for help, or suggestions for improving the project.

7. **Action items and follow-up (2 minutes)**: The team leader should summarize any action items or decisions made during the meeting and assign follow-up tasks to team members as needed.

8. **Meeting adjournment (1 minute)**: The meeting should conclude with a quick round of thanks and a reminder to keep the meeting minutes and action items in mind for the day's work.

instruction: Give a grammar tip on how to end a German verb.
output_1:
In German, verbs can be inflected to indicate the tense, mood, and person of the subject. To end a German verb, you need to add the appropriate ending based on the tense and person of the subject. Here are some general rules:

- For the present tense, add the ending "-e" for the first person singular (I) and "-en" for all other persons. For example, "ich lache" (I laugh) and "wir lachen" (we laugh).
- For the past tense, add the ending "-te" for the first person singular (I) and "-ten" for all other persons. For example, "ich lachte" (I laughed) and "wir lachten" (we laughed).
- For the future tense, add the ending "-e" for the first person singular (I) and "-en" for all other persons. For example, "ich lache" (I will laugh) and "wir lachen" (we will laugh).
- For the perfect tense, add the ending "-t" for the first person singular (I) and "-t" for all other persons. For example, "ich habe gelacht" (I have laughed) and "wir haben gelacht" (we have laughed).

It's important to note that there are many irregular verbs in German that do not follow these rules. Therefore, it's important to learn the specific endings for each verb.
output_2:
In German, verbs typically end in -en, -en, -e or -en- to indicate the past tense, depending on the verb. For example, in the past tense, the verb "essen" (to eat) would end in "-en," while the verb "sprechen" (to speak) would end in "-en-".

In addition to this, there are irregular verbs that have different past tense forms, such as "haben" (to have) which ends in "-en" in the present tense but changes to "-te" in the past tense.

It is essential to learn and memorize the correct ending for each verb to ensure proper grammar in written and spoken German.

instruction: Come up with healthy and easy dinner ideas for weeknights.
output_1:
1. Grilled chicken with roasted vegetables: Marinate chicken breasts in a mixture of olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, and herbs, then grill until cooked through. Roast vegetables such as zucchini, bell peppers, and onions in the oven with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Serve the chicken with the roasted vegetables.

2. Stuffed bell peppers: Cut bell peppers in half and remove seeds. Fill each pepper with a mixture of cooked quinoa, black beans, corn, and cheese. Bake in the oven until the cheese is melted and bubbly.

3. One-pot pasta: Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling water until al dente. Add a jar of marinara sauce and cooked ground beef or sausage. Add frozen peas and carrots and cook until heated through.

4. Baked salmon with asparagus: Season salmon fillets with salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Place on a baking sheet and bake in the oven until cooked through. Steam asparagus in the microwave until tender. Serve the salmon with the asparagus.

5. Slow cooker chili: Brown ground beef in a skillet and drain off excess fat. Add canned tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, and beans to the skillet and cook until heated through. Transfer the mixture to a slow cooker and cook on low for 6-8 hours. Serve with cornbread or tortilla chips.
output_2:
1. Grilled Chicken and Vegetable Skewers: Marinate chicken breasts in a mixture of olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, and herbs, then thread onto skewers with colorful vegetables such as bell peppers, onions, and zucchini. Grill until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender. Serve with a side salad.
2. One-Pot Pasta: Cook pasta in a large pot with a jar of marinara sauce and your favorite vegetables such as cherry tomatoes, mushrooms, and spinach. Serve with a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.
3. Black Bean and Sweet Potato Tacos: Cook black beans and sweet potatoes in a pan with a spicy tomato sauce, then serve in warm tortillas with toppings of your choice such as avocado, salsa, and sour cream.
4. Slow Cooker Lentil Soup: Cook lentils in a slow cooker with vegetables such as onions, carrots, and celery, then add chicken broth and spices. Serve with a side salad or crusty bread.
5. Roasted Vegetable Quinoa Bowl: Toss cooked quinoa with roasted vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower, and red bell pepper, then top with a sprinkle of feta cheese and a drizzle of olive oil.

instruction:
Describe how to prepare the given food in your own words. Note down the ingredients you will need and the steps you will take to prepare them.

Chewy Chocolate Chip Cookies
output_1:
To prepare chewy chocolate chip cookies, you will need the following ingredients:

Ingredients:
- 2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour
- 1 tsp baking soda
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 cup unsalted butter, softened
- 1/2 cup white sugar
- 1/2 cup brown sugar
- 1 tsp vanilla extract
- 2 large eggs
- 2 cups semisweet chocolate chips

Steps:

1. Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, and salt.

3. In a large bowl, cream together the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until light and fluffy.

4. Beat in the vanilla extract.

5. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.

6. Gradually mix in the dry ingredients until just combined.

7. Fold in the chocolate chips.

8. Drop the dough by tablespoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.

9. Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the edges are lightly golden.

10. Remove from the oven and let cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.

Enjoy your delicious chewy chocolate chip cookies!
output_2:
To prepare chewy chocolate chip cookies, you will need the following ingredients: 1 cup all-purpose flour, 3/4 cup granulated sugar, 1/2 cup unsalted butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 2 large eggs, 1 teaspoon baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips, and 1/4 cup chopped walnuts (optional).

1. Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
2. In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.
3. In a large bowl, cream together the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
4. Beat in the eggs one at a time, making sure each one is fully incorporated before adding the next.
5. Gradually mix in the dry ingredients, alternating with the chocolate chips and walnuts, if using.
6. The dough should be sticky and slightly crumbly. If it seems too dry, add a little water, one tablespoon at a time.
7. Using a cookie scoop or spoon, drop rounded tablespoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.
8. Bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the edges are lightly golden and the centers are set.
9. Remove from the oven and allow to cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.
10. Once cooled, store in an airtight container for up to one week.

instruction: Suggest a recipe for a vegan dessert.
output_1:
One delicious vegan dessert recipe is for a Chocolate Avocado Mousse. Here's what you'll need:

Ingredients:
- 1 ripe avocado
- 1/2 cup of cocoa powder
- 1/2 cup of almond milk
- 1/2 cup of maple syrup
- 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla extract
- 1/2 cup of fresh berries (such as strawberries, blueberries, or raspberries)

Instructions:
1. Begin by mashing the avocado in a bowl until it's smooth and creamy.
2. Add the cocoa powder, almond milk, maple syrup, and vanilla extract to the mashed avocado and mix well.
3. Chill the mixture in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.
4. Just before serving, gently fold in the fresh berries.
5. Serve the chocolate avocado mousse in small bowls or ramekins and enjoy!

This dessert is not only vegan but also gluten-free, dairy-free, and low in calories. The combination of chocolate and avocado creates a rich and creamy texture that's both indulgent and healthy. The fresh berries add a sweet and tangy contrast to the mousse, making it a perfect dessert for any occasion.
output_2:
Vegan Chocolate Avocado Mousse

Ingredients:
- 1 ripe avocado
- 1/4 cup coconut oil
- 1/4 cup maple syrup
- 1/4 cup almond milk
- 1 tsp vanilla extract
- 1 cup dark chocolate chips
- 1 cup frozen berries
- 1 tbsp coconut oil
- 1 tbsp maple syrup
- 1 tbsp almond milk

Instructions:
1. In a blender, blend the avocado, coconut oil, maple syrup, and almond milk until smooth.
2. Add the vanilla extract and blend again.
3. Pour the mixture into a bowl and refrigerate for 15 minutes to chill.
4. In a separate bowl, melt the dark chocolate chips and coconut oil in the microwave for about 30 seconds.
5. Remove the chocolate mixture and stir in the frozen berries.
6. Pour the chocolate mixture into a separate bowl and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
7. Remove both bowls from the refrigerator and carefully fold the chilled chocolate mixture into the avocado mousse.
8. Pour the mixture into serving dishes and refrigerate for at least 1 hour to chill.
9. Before serving, top with additional frozen berries and a drizzle of maple syrup.

Enjoy your delicious vegan chocolate avocado mousse!

instruction:
Solve this equation.

x^3 - 4x^2 + 6x - 24 = 0
output_2:
To solve this equation, we can use the quadratic formula: 

x = (-4 ± √(16^2 - 4(1)(-24))) / (2(1))

x = (-4 ± √(256 - 96)) / 2

x = (-4 ± √16) / 2

x = (-4 ± 4) / 2

x = 0 ± 2

x = 0, 2

Therefore, the solutions to the equation x^3 - 4x^2 + 6x - 24 = 0 are x = 0 and x = 2.

Let x be a positive integer or a solution to x+3>4.

If x is a positive integer, then x>0 and x>12 are true by definition.

If x is a solution to x+3>4, then x+3>4 is true. Since x+3>4 is equivalent to x>-3, we can substitute x=-3 into the equation to get -3+3>4, which is true. Therefore, x>-3 and x>12 are true.

Therefore, we can conclude that if x is a positive integer or a solution to x+3>4, then x>0 and x>12.

A study published earlier this year by Zee and her team examined the role of light in sleep for healthy adults in their 20s. Sleeping for only one night with a dim light, such as a TV set with the sound off, raised the blood sugar and heart rate of the young people during the sleep lab experiment. An elevated heart rate at night has been shown in prior studies to be a risk factor for future heart disease and early death, while higher blood sugar levels are a sign of insulin resistance, which can ultimately lead to type 2 diabetes.
output_1: The article discusses a study conducted by Zee and her team that examined the impact of light on sleep for healthy adults in their 20s. The study found that sleeping with a dim light, such as a TV set with the sound off, raised the blood sugar and heart rate of the young participants during the sleep lab experiment. This elevated heart rate at night is a risk factor for future heart disease and early death, while higher blood sugar levels are a sign of insulin resistance, which can lead to type 2 diabetes.
output_2: The article discusses a study conducted by Zee and her team that investigated the impact of light on sleep in healthy adults aged 20. During the sleep lab experiment, participants who slept under dim light conditions such as a TV with the sound off experienced increased blood sugar and heart rate, both of which are associated with increased risk of future heart disease, heart attacks, and death. The study highlights the importance of maintaining a dark sleep environment to support healthy sleep patterns and overall wellbeing.

instruction:
Describe the responsibilities of the given job.

Security Officer
output_1:
The responsibilities of a Security Officer typically include the following:

1. Ensuring the safety and security of people and property: This involves patrolling designated areas, monitoring surveillance cameras, and responding to any security breaches or emergencies.

2. Enforcing rules and regulations: Security officers are responsible for enforcing rules and regulations set by the organization or property owner, such as access control, parking regulations, and no-smoking policies.

3. Providing customer service: Security officers often interact with the public, so they must be able to provide a high level of customer service, including answering questions, providing directions, and assisting with any issues or concerns.

4. Monitoring and reporting suspicious activity: Security officers are responsible for monitoring the environment for any suspicious or unusual activity, and reporting any incidents to the appropriate authorities.

5. Maintaining security equipment: Security officers must be familiar with and maintain all security equipment, such as access control systems, surveillance cameras, and alarm systems.

6. Conducting security checks: Security officers may be responsible for conducting security checks, such as bag searches or ID verification, at designated areas or events.

7. Providing escort services: Security officers may be required to provide escort services for individuals or groups, such as visitors or employees, to ensure their safety and security.

Overall, the responsibilities of a Security Officer involve ensuring the safety and security of people and property, enforcing rules and regulations, providing customer service, monitoring and reporting suspicious activity, maintaining security equipment, conducting security checks, and providing escort services.
output_2:
The responsibilities of a Security Officer typically include the following tasks:

1. Ensuring the safety and security of people and property: This includes monitoring and patrolling designated areas, conducting regular security checks, and identifying and reporting potential security threats.

2. Enforcing security policies and procedures: The Security Officer is responsible for ensuring that all individuals and vehicles entering the premises follow established security protocols and guidelines.

3. Providing customer service: Security Officers often interact with visitors and employees, providing information and assistance as needed.

4. Responding to emergencies: In the event of an emergency, such as a fire or medical emergency, the Security Officer must take appropriate action to ensure the safety of everyone on the premises.

5. Maintaining communication with law enforcement: Security Officers may be required to communicate with local law enforcement agencies, providing information and assistance as needed.

6. Conducting regular inspections: Security Officers are responsible for conducting regular inspections of security systems and equipment, and reporting any issues or concerns to the appropriate authorities.

7. Maintaining accurate records: Security Officers must keep accurate records of security incidents, including reports, logs, and other relevant documentation.

Overall, the primary responsibility of a Security Officer is to ensure the safety and security of the premises, personnel, and assets under their care, through the enforcement of established security policies and procedures, and by maintaining effective communication and coordination with other security personnel and local law enforcement agencies.

instruction:

output_1:
Here is a list of skills that may help you find a job as a crew member:

1. Customer service skills: The ability to provide excellent customer service is essential for crew members as they are often the first point of contact for customers.

2. Communication skills: Good communication skills are important for crew members as they need to be able to communicate effectively with customers, colleagues, and management.

3. Teamwork: Crew members often work in teams, so the ability to work well with others is crucial.

4. Time management: Crew members need to be able to manage their time effectively to ensure that tasks are completed on time and to a high standard.

5. Attention to detail: Crew members need to be able to pay attention to detail to ensure that tasks are completed accurately and to a high standard.

6. Flexibility: Crew members may be required to work different shifts and be flexible with their availability.

7. Physical fitness: Crew members may be required to stand for long periods, lift heavy objects, and move quickly, so physical fitness is important.

8. Basic computer skills: Crew members may be required to use computer systems to complete tasks such as taking orders or tracking inventory.

9. Restaurant or retail experience: Experience in the restaurant or retail industry can be beneficial for crew members as it provides a good understanding of the industry and the expectations of customers.

10. Positive attitude: A positive attitude and a willingness to learn are important for crew members as they are often the face of the company and need to be able to handle difficult situations with a smile.

2. Ability to work in a fast-paced environment
3. Good communication and interpersonal skills
4. Teamwork and collaboration
5. Time management and organizational skills
6. Attention to detail and accuracy
7. Flexibility and adaptability

instruction:
Give a brief explanation of the requested part of the paper.

Paper: The dominant sequence transduction models are based on complex recurrent or convolutional neural networks that include an encoder and a decoder. The best performing models also connect the encoder and decoder through an attention mechanism. We propose a new simple network architecture, the Transformer, based solely on attention mechanisms, dispensing with recurrence and convolutions entirely. Experiments on two machine translation tasks show these models to be superior in quality while being more parallelizable and requiring significantly less time to train. Our model achieves 28.4 BLEU on the WMT 2014 English-to-German translation task, improving over the existing best results, including ensembles, by over 2 BLEU. On the WMT 2014 English-to-French translation task, our model establishes a new single-model state-of-the-art BLEU score of 41.8 after training for 3.5 days on eight GPUs, a small fraction of the training costs of the best models from the literature. We show that the Transformer generalizes well to other tasks by applying it successfully to English constituency parsing both with large and limited training data.
Explain: The dominant sequence transduction models
output_1: The paper discusses the current state-of-the-art sequence transduction models, which are based on complex recurrent or convolutional neural networks that include an encoder and a decoder. These models also use an attention mechanism to connect the encoder and decoder. The authors propose a new simple network architecture called the Transformer, which is based solely on attention mechanisms and does not use recurrence or convolutions. The paper evaluates the performance of the Transformer on two machine translation tasks and compares it to existing models. The results show that the Transformer outperforms existing models in quality while being more parallelizable and requiring less time to train. The paper also demonstrates the generalization of the Transformer to other tasks such as English constituency parsing.
output_2: The paper discusses the current state of the art in sequence transduction models, specifically those used for machine translation tasks. These models are based on either complex recurrent neural networks (RNNs) or convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that include an encoder and a decoder, with the best performing models also incorporating attention mechanisms. The proposed new model, called the Transformer, replaces the RNNs and CNNs with attention mechanisms alone, resulting in a simpler architecture. The paper presents experiments on two machine translation tasks, showing that the proposed Transformer model outperforms the existing complex models with regard to quality, while being more parallelizable and faster to train. Additionally, the Transformer model achieves significantly better results on the English-to-German and English-to-French machine translation tasks, setting new state-of-the-art scores.

instruction: Recommend some helpful activities or conversation starters to use at meetups to break the ice.
output_1:
Here are some activities or conversation starters that can help break the ice at a meetup:

1. Icebreaker games: There are many icebreaker games that can be played at a meetup, such as Two Truths and a Lie, Would You Rather, or Herding Cats. These games are a fun way to get to know people and can be adapted to fit the group's interests.
2. Group challenges: Another way to break the ice is to have a group challenge, such as a scavenger hunt or a team-building exercise. This can be a fun way to get people to work together and get to know each other.
3. Group discussions: A group discussion can be a great way to get people talking and sharing their thoughts and ideas. You could start with a general topic and then allow the conversation to flow naturally, or you could provide a list of discussion topics to choose from.
4. Speed networking: Speed networking is a structured way to meet a large number of people in a short amount of time. You could set up a series of one-on-one or small group conversations, or you could have a more informal "speed dating" style event.
5. Group activities: You could also plan group activities, such as a potluck dinner, a group outing to a local attraction, or a volunteer project. These activities can be a fun way to bond with others and get to know them in a more relaxed setting.

Remember, the key to breaking the ice at a meetup is to create a welcoming and inclusive environment where people feel comfortable sharing their thoughts and ideas.
output_2:
Meetups can be a great way to connect with like-minded people and make new friends. Here are some helpful activities or conversation starters that you could use to break the ice at a meetup:

1. Introduce yourself: Start by introducing yourself to everyone in the group. Share your name, where you're from, and what brought you to the meetup.
2. Icebreaker games: There are many icebreaker games that can help people get to know each other. Examples include "Two Truths and a Lie," "Speed Dating," or "Acquaintance Bingo."
3. Group discussion: Start a group discussion on a topic that everyone can relate to. It could be a common interest, a recent news story, or a current event.
4. Share a personal story: Share a personal story or experience that is relevant to the group or the meetup theme. This can help people connect with you on a personal level.
5. Ask questions: Ask open-ended questions that encourage people to share their thoughts and opinions. Examples could include "What's your favorite book?" or "What's the best advice you've ever received?"
6. Group activity: Plan a group activity, such as a scavenger hunt, a cooking class, or a volunteer project. This can help people bond and work together towards a common goal.
7. Share your favorite quote or inspiration: Share a favorite quote or inspiring message that resonates with you. This can help spark interesting conversations and connections.

Remember, the key is to create a welcoming and inclusive environment where everyone feels comfortable sharing their thoughts and ideas.

instruction:
Extract the method that has been used in the research from the abstract of the paper. Give the exact sentences from the abstract that discuss the method.

We present a state-of-the-art speech recognition system developed using end-to-end deep learning. Our architecture is significantly simpler than traditional speech systems, which rely on laboriously engineered processing pipelines; these traditional systems also tend to perform poorly when used in noisy environments. In contrast, our system does not need hand-designed components to model background noise, reverberation, or speaker variation, but instead directly learns a function that is robust to such effects. We do not need a phoneme dictionary, nor even the concept of a "phoneme." Key to our approach is a well-optimized RNN training system that uses multiple GPUs, as well as a set of novel data synthesis techniques that allow us to efficiently obtain a large amount of varied data for training. Our system, called Deep Speech, outperforms previously published results on the widely studied Switchboard Hub5'00, achieving 16.0% error on the full test set. Deep Speech also handles challenging noisy environments better than widely used, state-of-the-art commercial speech systems.Collapse

The method used is a well-optimized RNN training system that uses multiple GPUs, and novel data synthesis techniques to obtain a large amount of varied data for training. The architecture is significantly simpler than traditional speech systems, and does not require hand-designed components to model background noise, reverberation, or speaker variation.
